title: Aquatics: Swimming Level I
description: Coeducational. Primary skills development. Course is designed to teach ''non-swimmers'' how to swim better. The following is taught: Red Cross swimming instruction in overcoming fears, water adjustment, floating, breath holding, and rhythmic breathing. Skills to be learned are: water entries, sculling, treading, elementary backstroke, freestyle, methods of water safety, and survival techniques. Prerequisite(s): instructor determines skill level at first class meeting.
class_notes: No prior swim experience required. This course is designed for beginners and those just learning to swim. Attend first class prepared for activity, for evaluation and permission codes.
